OL,5, A West End production of Slave Play    
OL,6, that plans to host some shows for black
OL,7, audiences only has been criticised by  
OL,8, Downing Street as "wrong and divisive".
OL,10,FThe Noel Coward Theatre will hold two  
OL,11,F"Black Out" performances solely for an 
OL,12,F"all-black-identifying audience".      
OL,14,FSet on a plantation in the old American
OL,15,FSouth, the controversial play explores 
OL,16,F"race, identity and sexuality".        
OL,18,FWritten by US actor and playwright     
OL,19,FJeremy O Harris, it has received more  
OL,20,FTony nominations than any other play.  
